  "texts": [
    "GSL is designed to jointly learn an optimized graph structure and corresponding adjacency matrix [36].",
    "Based on the assumption that edges tend to connect nodes with similar representation, the proposed method refines the input graphs by computing the similarity between the last updated node embedding pairs, which are then used as the edge weights.Euclidean distance is no longer an effective metric for graph node similarity.",
    "Instead, a generalized adaptive Mahalanobis distance is employed to quantify node similarity, as formulated in (3):φ(z i, z j) = z i -z j T W d W T d z i -z j,(3)where z i, z j denote the embedding of two node i and j learned in the last graph snapshot, and W d is a trainable weight.",
    "W d W T d constructs a symmetric positive semidefinite trainable parameter.",
    "Mahalanobis distance can adaptively fit the task and the node embeddings during training."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "GSL is designed to jointly learn an optimized graph structure and corresponding adjacency matrix [36]."
  ]
